President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with the Sokoto Emirate Council and the government and people of Sokoto State over the death of the Sarkin Malaman Sokoto, Alhaji Buhari Siriddawa. Buhari, in a statement issued yesterday by his spokesman, Garba Shehu, said the death of Sarkin Malam Sokoto was not only a loss to the people of Sokoto State but the entire country because of his indefatigable commitment to peace during his life on earth. The president said the late Siriddawa had committed himself to the promotion of peace, unity, tolerance and peaceful coexistence in the country. He described the deceased as a remarkable leader who built an enviable legacy worthy of emulation. He prayed that Almighty Allah forgives his soul, rewards his noble deeds with paradise, and grants the family the fortitude to bear the loss. Senator Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko also extolled the Sheikh Buhari Siriddawa’s “legendary, unparalleled, and unprecedented” commitment to the growth and development of the country. “He was always available, open, untiring, unrelenting, dogged and religiously committed to the cause of Islam,” he said. Special prayer for peaceful polls holds in Sokoto Insecurity: Buhari renews pledge to end killings Buhari condoles Sokoto over Wamakko''s death